● Even a silent hang may have left a pstore record (slub_debug=FZP trips at the
  bad write, which is earlier than any visible oops). Please run:

  sudo ls -1t /var/lib/systemd/pstore/
  sudo journalctl -k -b -1 --no-pager | tail -200

  Then paste the output. Specifically I want:
  1. Whether any new dmesg-* files exist in pstore from the hang.
  2. The tail of the previous boot's kernel log — if the panic fired but the
  framebuffer was already dead, the message will still be in the journal from
  the previous boot.

  If pstore is empty and the previous-boot journal ends cleanly with no oops,
  that points away from SLUB corruption and toward a hard hardware/firmware
  lockup — different remediation path (firmware/driver bisect, not memory
  debug).

